<en-export export-date="20260611T074023Z" application="Evernote" version="11.9.1">
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180823T051406Z</created>
    <updated>20230801T094154Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">Angioleiomyoma</span></span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br/></span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">Microscopic description:</span></span></span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 16px;"><span style="font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial;">Section shows one well-defined nodular lesion composed of proliferative muscle bundles and compressed vessels.</span></span></span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Angiolipoma [angiolipo]</title>
    <created>20170612T051722Z</created>
    <updated>20230713T031351Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">angiolipoma.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Sections show mature fat cells incorporated with numerous proliferating capillaries.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Arteriovenous malformation. [AVM]</title>
    <created>20210517T045059Z</created>
    <updated>20230830T050402Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div>Arteriovenous malformation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows vessels in different sizes of the vascular wall. One dilated vessel with abrupt changes in thickness of vascular wall is seen. Thrombosis is seen in the lumen. The overall features are consistent with arteriovenous malformation. By immunohistochemistry, the endothelial cells are highlighted by ERG and CD31.</div><hr/><div>Arteriovenous malformation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows arterioles, capillaries, and venules intermixed with larger-calibre, tortuous vein. By immunohistochemistry, the endothelial cells are highlighted by CD31. The overall features are consistent with arteriovenous malformation.</div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>Arteriovenous malformation</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows vessels in different sizes of the vascular wall. One dilated vessel with abrupt changes in thickness of vascular wall is seen. Thrombosis is seen in the lumen. The overall features are consistent with arteriovenous malformation. No malignancy is</div><div>observed.</div><div><br/></div></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Atypical lipomatous tumor ALT</title>
    <created>20170102T080037Z</created>
    <updated>20230526T042718Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Atypical lipomatous tumor</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show adipocytes with variation in size and presence of atypical hyperchromatic stromal cells in a myxoid stroma. The surgical margin is involved.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the atypical cells are positive for CDK4.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Benign notochordal cell tumor (BNCT).</title>
    <created>20170206T004620Z</created>
    <updated>20170206T004632Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>The biopsy shows sheets of large polyhedral cells with abundant clear to pale pink cytoplasm with round nuclei containing fine or homogeneously dense chromatin. There is no myxoid extracellular matrix. Immunohistochemical studies show that the tumor cells are positive for S-100, keratin and brachyury. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Bursitis</title>
    <created>20170217T062147Z</created>
    <updated>20250110T061450Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: gotham;">bursitis.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Section shows a cystic lesion surrounded by fibrous tissue with chronic inflammatory infiltrate and capillary proliferation.</span></div><div><br/></div><hr/><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Soft tissue,___, bursectomy --- bursitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of _ pieces of tissue measuring up to _ cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a cystic lesion surrounded by fibrous tissue with chronic inflammatory infiltrate and capillary proliferation.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Cavernous hemangioma</title>
    <created>20170215T095633Z</created>
    <updated>20250507T082511Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="padding-left:40px;">Cavernous hemangioma.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Microscopic description:</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Section shows a demarcated nodule composed of cystically dilated vessels filled with blood.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Confirmed, _ carpal ligament, transverse ligament release</title>
