    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows dense connective tissue consistent with ligament.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20190703T052706Z</created>
    <updated>20241204T061342Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with calcific tendonitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows extensive calcific deposits focally surrounded by histiocytes, consistent with calcific tendonitis.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20181211T101953Z</created>
    <updated>20181211T102002Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with synovial cyst.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a cyst formed by a fibrous connective tissue</div><div>wall focally lined by histiocytes and containing blood clots</div><div>and fibrinoid deposition in its lumen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>De-Quervain&apos;s disease</title>
    <created>20200409T031823Z</created>
    <updated>20251014T093257Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>
        https://www.google.com/search?rlz=1C1BEMX_zh-TWTW773TW773&amp;ei=1ZOOXo7EJ8X7-Qa27pH4BQ&amp;q=tenovaginectomy&amp;oq=tenovaginectomy&amp;gs_lcp=CgZwc3ktYWIQAzoECAAQEzoICAAQDRAeEBNKDAgXEggxMC02MGc0NEoKCBgSBjEwLTJnMVDTLljrMWDYNGgAcAB4AIABQIgBnQGSAQEzmAEAoAEBqgEHZ3dzLXdpeg&amp;sclient=psy-ab&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjOgpv6sNroAhXFfd4KHTZ3BF8Q4dUDCAw&amp;uact=5
      </source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Soft tissue, ____wrist, tenovaginectomy ---</div><div>Consistent with De-Quervain's disease. See description.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of 3 pieces of grayish tissue measuring 0.7x0.3x0.3 cm in size.</div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows thickening and myxoid degeneration of tendon consistent with a chronic degenerative process, as opposed to inflammation. These findings are consistent but not pathognomonic for De-Quervain's disease.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>dermatofibrosarcoma protuberans.</title>
    <created>20221017T044652Z</created>
    <updated>20240927T050720Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>dermatofibrosarcoma protuberans.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Tumor type: dermatofibrosarcoma protuberans.</div><div>Tumor size: 2.6 cm at greatest dimension</div><div>Tumor location: lower abdominal wall, within dermis and</div><div>  subcutis</div><div>Mitotic rate: 1/10 high-power fields (HPF).</div><div>Necrosis: absent.</div><div>Surgical margin: involved at peripheral and deep margins.</div><div>Immunohistochemical studies:</div><div>  SMA: weakly positive.</div><div>  Desmin, S100: negative</div><div>  CD34: positive</div><div>  Beta-catenin: no nuclear expression.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been reviewed by two pathologists.) </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210504T025906Z</created>
    <updated>20210504T025921Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>desmoplastic fibroblastoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows well-circumscribed, lobulated lesions which shows patternless proliferation of bland spindle or stellate cells in a hypovascular fibrous stroma.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20201105T064119Z</created>
    <updated>20211129T075141Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>
        https://www.google.com/search?q=digital+mucous+cyst++ganglion+cyst&amp;rlz=1C1BEMX_zh-TWTW773TW773&amp;ei=KYWkYf7VOaiymAX1mKiwCw&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi-jq2Hir30AhUoGaYKHXUMCrYQ4dUDCA4&amp;uact=5&amp;oq=digital+mucous+cyst++ganglion+cyst&amp;gs_lcp=Cgdnd3Mtd2l6EAMyBAgAEB4yBggAEAgQHjoLCAAQsAMQzQIQiwNKBQg8EgEzSgQIQRgBSgQIRhgAUNAKWK0NYI4OaANwAHgAgAE7iAHVAZIBATSYAQCgAQHIAQG4AQLAAQE&amp;sclient=gws-wiz
      </source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>digital mucous cyst.                 </div><div>                   </div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The cyst is formed by a fibrous connective tissue wall without epithelial lining.</div><div><br/></div><div>This is a digital mucous cyst, as known as benign ganglion cysts of the digits.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Endometriosis</title>
    <created>20170615T054624Z</created>
    <updated>20250731T061404Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Endometriosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show soft tissue with embedded endometrial glands and stromal cells,</div><div>accompanied by aggregate of hemosiderin-laden macrophages. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Epithelioid hemangioma (angiolymphoid hyperplasia with eosinophilia)</title>
    <created>20181102T021321Z</created>
    <updated>20181102T021336Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Epithelioid hemangioma (angiolymphoid hyperplasia with eosinophilia)</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows skin tissue revealing lobular proliferation of capillaries surrounding central vessel in the subcutaneous layer. The capillaries are lined by plump, epithelioid endothelial cells without nuclear pleomorphism. There is abundant infiltrate of eosinophils and lymphocytes, accompanied by focal lymphoid follicle formation with reactive germinal centers at periphery of lesion. Staining for HHV-8 is negative. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Fibrolipoma</title>
    <created>20161227T041416Z</created>
    <updated>20210513T042906Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>lipoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The mass is composed of closely-packed mature fat cells admixed with fibrous tissue component.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Fibroma of tendon sheath</title>
    <created>20170724T083152Z</created>
    <updated>20210715T060927Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Fibroma of tendon sheath.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a demarcated nodule composed of hyalinized, collagenous matrix</div><div>associated with widely dispersed spindle cells and thin-walled blood vessels. The</div><div>spindled cells are devoid of nuclear atypia and mitotic activity.</div><div>    </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
