  <note>
    <title>GAN benign fibroadipose tissue, clinically ganglion</title>
    <created>20230804T080416Z</created>
    <updated>20260213T045851Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Benign fibroadipose tissue, clinically ganglion.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows fibroadipose tissue including some thick-walled blood vessels. No obvious cystic wall is included.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>GAN Ganglion cyst</title>
    <created>20170509T052024Z</created>
    <updated>20230804T080413Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Ganglion cyst.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The cyst is formed by a fibrous connective tissue wall without epithelial lining.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Glomus tumor</title>
    <created>20220309T040012Z</created>
    <updated>20250604T022955Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Glomus tumor.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows capillary sized vessels lined by endothelial</div><div>cells surrounded by uniform glomus cells forming nests and</div><div>sheets in a hyalinized stroma. Glomus cell has a round shape</div><div>with indistinct borders with eosinophilic cytoplasm</div><div>Immunohistochemically, CD34 and SMA are positive, consistent</div><div>with the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180518T073605Z</created>
    <updated>20250226T052815Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Gouty tophi</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The section reveals collection of amorphous urate crystal deposits in irregular</div><div>islands partly surrounded by granulomatous inflammatory infiltrates consisting of</div><div>lymphocytes, plasma cells, epithelioid histiocytes and multinucleated giant cells.</div><div>    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Gouty tophi with suppurative inflammation</title>
    <created>20170331T051042Z</created>
    <updated>20200528T071651Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Gouty tophi with suppurative inflammation</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The section reveals collection of amorphous urate crystal deposits in irregular</div><div>islands partly surrounded by mild granulomatous inflammatory infiltrates consisting of</div><div>lymphocytes, plasma cells, epithelioid histiocytes and multinucleated giant cells.</div><div>Besides, suppurative inflam<span>    </span>mation is also noted. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Graft infection / ESRD</title>
    <created>20220512T081735Z</created>
    <updated>20220512T081754Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Suppurative inflammation and foreign body reaction.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows suppurative inflammation with collections of</div><div>neutrophils, liquified debris of necrotic cells and edema</div><div>fluid. Foreign body-like materials consistent with graft, along with aggregates of histiocytes and multinucleated giant cells are seen.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>HG sarcoma, DDx DDLPS, osteosarcoma</title>
    <created>20170623T080037Z</created>
    <updated>20170623T080054Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Section shows a high-grade sarcoma which is composed of fascicles of neoplastic spindle cells with marked cellular atypia and tumor necrosis. Focal deposition of lace-like osteoid is identified.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are diffusely and strongly positive for CDK4</div><div>but not AE1/AE3, desmin, or CD117. S100 shows a few scattered positive cells.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20220222T041305Z</created>
    <updated>20220222T041314Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Intramuscular angioma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows cystically dilated vessels with focal thrombosis and lined by bland endothelial cells admixed with mature adipose tissue within skeletal muscle tissue.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Intravascular fasciitis</title>
    <created>20170217T030011Z</created>
    <updated>20170217T030027Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows a well-demarcated subcutaneous nodule composed of plump and bland  spindle-shaped myofibroblasts arising from a vessel. Mitoses are seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the spindle cells are positive for smooth muscle actin, but negative for CD34, S-100, CD68, EMA or desmin. CD34 highlights the</div><div>intravascular growth of lesional cells. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Intravascular lobular capillary hemangioma</title>
    <created>20170117T011244Z</created>
    <updated>20170117T011257Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows intravascular proliferation of capillary-sized lobules of capillary channels lined by bland endothelial cells. Mitoses are occasionally seen. No malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180501T073556Z</created>
    <updated>20180501T073600Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
