    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>is</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Kaposi sarcoma.</title>
    <created>20201103T044956Z</created>
    <updated>20240229T030720Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Kaposi sarcoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows dermal cellular proliferation comprising fascicles of spindle cells with small slit-like spaces containing erythrocytes. These cells are uniform and contain minimally atypical elongated vesicular nuclei. Epidermal ulceration is seen. An infiltrate of neutrophils, lymphocytes and some plasma cells is seen.</div><div>Immunohistochemically, the spindle cells express CD31 and CD34 with focal loss of associated SMA-positive pericytes. Nuclear expression of HHV in spindle cells is seen, confirming the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Peripheral margin: _ mm.</div><div>Deep margin :__ mm.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Lipoma</title>
    <created>20210513T042849Z</created>
    <updated>20240222T083359Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Lipoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The mass is composed of closely-packed mature fat cells. No malignancy is observed.</div><div>    </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Lipoma_form</title>
    <created>20191014T052832Z</created>
    <updated>20230526T042614Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Soft tissue, _____, excision --- Lipoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of a piece of tissue measuring ____ cm. On cut section, it shows soft and yellowish cut surface without necrosis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are taken and submitted in one cassette.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The mass is composed of closely-packed mature fat cells. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Lobular capillary hemangioma</title>
    <created>20161222T005550Z</created>
    <updated>20231031T042332Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; float: none;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;">lobular capillary hemangioma.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; float: none;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; float: none;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;">Microscopic description:</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: small; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; float: none; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal;">Section shows a demarcated lesion composed of lobules of capillary channels lined by bland endothelial cells. Mitoses are occasionally seen. No malignancy is observed.<span>    </span></span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170222T080836Z</created>
    <updated>20230906T060540Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Multiple nodules of amorphous substance are encased by granulomatous response with histiocytes and foreign body giant cells.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Myopericytoma</title>
    <created>20181016T081720Z</created>
    <updated>20181016T082159Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><br/></div><div>Section shows a well-circumscribed tumor composed of uniform oval-to spindle-shaped tumor cells that display a multilayered, perivascular, concentric growth. The tumor cells contain eosinophilic cytoplasm and plump spindled nuclei. There are increased blood vessels which are</div><div>variable in size.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells express SMA  but not S-100, CD34 or desmin.</div><div><br/></div><div>Taken together, this is a myopericytoma, a benign neoplasm. There is no evidence of malilgnancy.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Necrotizing inflammation</title>
    <created>20161222T065439Z</created>
    <updated>20161222T065447Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows extensive and widespread tissue necrosis of the soft tissues accompanied by diffuse inflammatory cells infiltration. No malignancy is observed. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Neurofibroma</title>
    <created>20180313T051737Z</created>
    <updated>20260514T031936Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">neurofibroma</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Sections show skin tissue with a demarcated nodule composed of loosely arranged spindle cells in haphazard arrangement. </span>The lesional cells feature small, hyperchromatic, wavy or buckled nuclei in a variable myxoid to collagenous matrix.</div><div>No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Nodular fasciitis</title>
    <created>20170222T084528Z</created>
    <updated>20170222T084545Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows a subcutaneous nodule composed of plump and regular spindle-shaped  fibroblasts, arranged in fascicles and tissue culture-like pattern with focal</div><div>lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate. Collagen bundles are focally seen. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Nodular fasciitis</title>
    <created>20170213T021415Z</created>
    <updated>20250625T062705Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Nodular fasciitis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a subcutaneous nodule composed of plump and regular spindle-shaped  fibroblasts, arranged in fascicles and tissue culture-like pattern with focal</div><div>lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate. Collagen bundles are focally seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the spindle cells are positive for smooth muscle actin, but negative for CD34 and S-100. No malignancy is observed.</div><div>    </div><div><a href="https://share.evernote.com/note/50b2f951-2eb0-3b5f-9d85-cfcaa55803d6" rel="noopener noreferrer" rev="en_rl_none">Nodular fasciitis</a></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pericytes SMA</title>
    <created>20210820T022007Z</created>
    <updated>20260428T083021Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Immunohistochemically, the endothelial cells are highlighted by ERG with associated SMA-positive pericytes.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180925T054813Z</created>
    <updated>20241029T034646Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Plantar fibromatosis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows nodules and fascicles of uniform spindle cells with small nuclei in a collagenous stroma. Compressed vascular spaces are seen. The surgical margin is free but very close to the tumor (&lt;1mm).</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the spindle cells are positive for SMA, but not S100, CD34 or beta-catenin. Desmin is positive in scattered, individual cells.</div><div><br/></div><div>NOTE: The tumor shows a significant rate of local recurrence.</div><div><br/></div><div>Palmar fibromatosis</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>reactive myofibroblastic proliferation</title>
    <created>20211104T025034Z</created>
    <updated>20211104T025224Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-url>https://www.twiap.org.tw/pa/entrust/replyData.asp?Document_SID=9516</source-url>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(17, 17, 17);">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="box-sizing: border-box; display: inline-block; zoom: 1; width: 911.392px; min-height: 80px; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(17, 17, 17); line-height: 34px; vertical-align: top; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(225, 225, 225); position: relative; height: auto !important;">Section shows haphazard proliferation of reactive myofibroblasts.</span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Schwannoma</title>
    <created>20170315T235600Z</created>
    <updated>20240102T071456Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sections show a well-encapsulated partially cystic and partially solid tumor featuring</div><div>alternating hypocellular and hypercellualr areas composed of spindle cells with</div><div>indistinct cytoplasmic borders and elongated, wavy nuclei. Hyalinized blood vessels</div><div>are seen throughout the lesion. Striking nuclear atypia, favoring degenerative atypia,</div><div>with no increased mitotic activity is occasionally seen. Calcifications, hemosiderin-</div><div>laden cells and lymphoid aggregates are seen in the fibrous capsule.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Schwannoma</title>
    <created>20161222T234526Z</created>
    <updated>20251201T052219Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Schwannoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a demarcated and encapsulated tumor featuring alternating hypocellular and hypercellualr areas, composed of spindle cells with focal degenerative atypia. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div>Sections show a picture of schwannoma, which is composed of a biphasic tumor with compact areas of spindle cells (Antoni A pattern) showing occasional palisading, alternating with loosely arranged foci (Antoni B pattern) containing collections of lipid-laden histiocytes. Hemorrhage and cystic degeneration is present.</div><div><br/></div><div>By immunohistochemistry, the lesional cells are diffusely positive for S100, consistent with the diagnosis.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Schwannoma.</div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 14px;">Section shows alternating hypocellular and hypercellualr areas composed of spindle cells featuring indistinct cytoplasmic borders and elongated, wavy nuclei. Focal degenerative atypia, with no increased mitotic activity is also seen. Clusters of irregular vascular channels with hyalinized wall and calcification are also seen. No malignancy is observed.</span></span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><en-todo checked="false" /> Large vessels with thick hyalinized walls and luminal thrombi are also seen.</div><div><en-todo checked="false" />Immunohistochemically, the spindle cells show strong and diffuse S-100 expression with both nuclear and cytoplasmic staining. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Solitary fibrous tumor SFT</title>
    <created>20170808T052403Z</created>
    <updated>20250108T062020Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Solitary fibrous tumor.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections shows a well circumscribed tumor composed of alternating hypo- and hypercellular areas of bland-looking spindle cells, in a collagenous and vascularized stroma. Perivascular hyalinization is seen. Myxoid change is seen within hypocellular area.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically,</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>spindle cell hemangioma</title>
    <created>20240806T025033Z</created>
    <updated>20240929T150146Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>spindle cell hemangioma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show a well-circumscribed subcutaneous tumor composed of dilated cavernous-like vascular channels intermixed with solid areas composed of epithelioid and spindle endothelial cells. Vacuolated epithelioid endothelial cells are seen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the lesional cells are positive for ERG. Associated pericytes are highlighted by SMA.</div><div>HHV8 is negative.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Spindle cell lipoma</title>
    <created>20170804T015417Z</created>
    <updated>20231226T031649Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Spindle cell lipoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows a well-circumscribed mass composed of mature adipose tissue admixed</div><div>with bland spindle cells and "ropey" collagen.</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the spindle cells are positive for CD34 but not CDK4.</div><div>No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20181016T032255Z</created>
    <updated>20181016T032545Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Synovial metaplasia</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows cystic space with a lining identical to synovial tissue.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Tenolysis, tendon</title>
    <created>20190306T034158Z</created>
    <updated>20190306T034643Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>confirmed.<br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Setion shows dense connective tissue consistent with tendon.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170222T082808Z</created>
    <updated>20200213T075926Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tenosynovial giant cell tumor, diffuse type</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows villous or papillary structures lined by synoviocytes, with multinodular growth of bland-looking histocytoid cells, admixed with scattered osteoclast-like giant cells. There are focal collections of foamy histiocytes. Hemosiderin deposits are seen. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><hr/><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Tenosynovial giant cell tumor, diffuse type. See note.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show villous structure lined by synoviocytes, with multinodular or solid growth of bland-looking histocytoid cells, admixed with scattered osteoclast-like</div><div>giant cells and prominent foamy histiocytes. Hemosiderin deposits are seen. Focal necrosis is seen. However, no overt atypia is noted. The mitotic activity is around 4 per 10 HPFs.</div><div>No malignant transformation is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div>Note: Diffuse-type tenosynovial giant cell tumor is locally aggressive but non-metastasizing, with a recurrent rate of around 20-50%.</div></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Tenosynovial giant cell tumor, localized type TSGCT</title>
    <created>20170222T082808Z</created>
    <updated>20230629T054152Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">tenosynovial giant cell tumor, localized type.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows a well circumscribed tumor composed predominantly of bland-looking histiocytoid cells, accompanied by scattered osteoclast-like giant cells. There are focal collections of foamy histiocytes. No malignancy is observed.<span>    </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Thrombectomy</title>
    <created>20180622T065328Z</created>
    <updated>20231114T055607Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Consistent with thrombus</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows fibrinoid deposition admixed with some neutrophils and eosinophils.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Varicose vein</title>
    <created>20170206T053647Z</created>
    <updated>20181011T062728Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Varicose vein</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The vessels show fibrotic wall with marked variation in thickness with thinning at</div><div>points of maximal dilatation.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Section shows dilated blood vessels of varying sizes with irregular thin to thick walls. No atypical change of the endothelial cells is noted.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
</en-export>
